 Butterworth police arrested a 36-year-old man for possession of dagga worth nearly R1 million over the weekend. "The suspect was arrested on Sunday, at about 16:00, at Ndabakazi Station outside Butterworth," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The dagga has weight of 810 kg with a street value of R900 000." He said that the suspect was arrested following police intelligence. "The suspect will appear before the Butterworth Magistrate's Court on Monday on a charge of possession of dagga." 